<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Vulnerabilities - Pwnshop</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.11.3/font/bootstrap-icons.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Syne:wght@400;600;700;800&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        :root {
            --purple-deep:  #3B0764;
            --purple-mid:   #6D28D9;
            --purple-light: #A855F7;
            --purple-pale:  #F3E8FF;
            --black:        #0D0D0D;
            --white:        #FFFFFF;
            --gray-100:     #F8F5FF;
            --gray-200:     #EDE9F6;
            --gray-500:     #6B7280;
            --gray-700:     #374151;
            --accent:       #C026D3;
            --critical:     #7f1d1d;
            --critical-bg:  #fef2f2;
            --critical-bd:  #fecaca;
            --high:         #7c2d12;
            --high-bg:      #fff7ed;
            --high-bd:      #fed7aa;
            --medium:       #713f12;
            --medium-bg:    #fefce8;
            --medium-bd:    #fde68a;
            --info:         #1e3a5f;
            --info-bg:      #eff6ff;
            --info-bd:      #bfdbfe;
        }
        * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
        body { font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; background: var(--gray-100); color: var(--black); min-height: 100vh; }
        code { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.82em; background: rgba(109,40,217,0.07); color: var(--purple-mid); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 4px; }

        /* ── NAVBAR ── */
        .topbar { background: var(--purple-deep); padding: 0; position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 1000; box-shadow: 0 2px 16px rgba(59,7,100,0.4); }
        .topbar .container { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 16px; padding: 12px 24px; }
        .navbar-brand { font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-weight: 800; font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--white) !important; text-decoration: none; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; }
        .navbar-brand .dot { width: 8px; height: 8px; background: var(--purple-light); border-radius: 50%; }
        .nav-right { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; list-style: none; margin: 0 0 0 auto; padding: 0; }
        .nav-link-plain { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.75) !important; font-size: 0.88rem; padding: 6px 12px; border-radius: 6px; text-decoration: none; }
        .nav-link-plain:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1); color: var(--white) !important; }
        .user-chip { text-decoration: none; background: rgba(168,85,247,0.2); border: 1px solid rgba(168,85,247,0.4); color: var(--white) !important; border-radius: 20px; padding: 5px 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; }
        .btn-logout { background: transparent; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3); color: rgba(255,255,255,0.8) !important; border-radius: 8px; padding: 5px 12px; font-size: 0.83rem; text-decoration: none; }

        /* ── HERO ── */
        .hero { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--purple-deep) 0%, #1e1b4b 100%); padding: 52px 0 44px; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); }
        .hero-inner { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; }
        .hero-eyebrow { font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1.5px; color: var(--purple-light); margin-bottom: 10px; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 7px; }
        .hero-title { font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-weight: 800; font-size: 2rem; color: var(--white); margin-bottom: 10px; line-height: 1.2; }
        .hero-sub { font-size: 0.9rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55); line-height: 1.65; max-width: 560px; margin-bottom: 28px; }
        .hero-stats { display: flex; gap: 32px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
        .hero-stat { }
        .hero-stat .num { font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-weight: 800; font-size: 1.6rem; color: var(--white); line-height: 1; }
        .hero-stat .lbl { font-size: 0.72rem; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.45); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; margin-top: 3px; }

        /* ── LAYOUT ── */
        .page-wrap { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 36px 24px 80px; }

        /* ── FILTER BAR ── */
        .filter-bar { display: flex; gap: 6px; margin-bottom: 28px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
        .filter-btn { background: var(--white); border: 1.5px solid var(--gray-200); color: var(--gray-500); border-radius: 8px; padding: 6px 14px; font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.18s; font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; }
        .filter-btn:hover { border-color: var(--purple-mid); color: var(--purple-mid); background: var(--purple-pale); }
        .filter-btn.active { background: var(--purple-deep); border-color: var(--purple-deep); color: var(--white); }

        /* ── CATEGORY HEADER ── */
        .cat-header { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin: 32px 0 14px; }
        .cat-header h2 { font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.78rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 1px; color: var(--gray-500); margin: 0; }
        .cat-header::after { content: ''; flex: 1; height: 1px; background: var(--gray-200); }

        /* ── VULN CARD ── */
        .vuln-card { background: var(--white); border-radius: 12px; border: 1.5px solid var(--gray-200); margin-bottom: 10px; overflow: hidden; transition: border-color 0.18s, box-shadow 0.18s; }
        .vuln-card:hover { border-color: var(--purple-light); box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(109,40,217,0.08); }
        .vuln-card-head { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px; padding: 16px 20px; cursor: pointer; user-select: none; }
        .vuln-card-head::-webkit-details-marker { display: none; }
        /* severity shown via left border on card head */
        .vuln-card[data-sev="critical"] .vuln-card-head { border-left: 3px solid #dc2626; }
        .vuln-card[data-sev="high"]     .vuln-card-head { border-left: 3px solid #ea580c; }
        .vuln-card[data-sev="medium"]   .vuln-card-head { border-left: 3px solid #ca8a04; }
        .vuln-card[data-sev="info"]     .vuln-card-head { border-left: 3px solid #2563eb; }
        .vuln-id { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--gray-500); background: var(--gray-100); border: 1px solid var(--gray-200); border-radius: 5px; padding: 2px 7px; white-space: nowrap; }
        .vuln-title { font-family: 'Syne', sans-serif; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--black); flex: 1; }
        .sev-badge { font-size: 0.65rem; font-weight: 700; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; border-radius: 5px; padding: 3px 8px; white-space: nowrap; }
        .sev-critical { background: var(--critical-bg); color: var(--critical); border: 1px solid var(--critical-bd); }
        .sev-high     { background: var(--high-bg);     color: var(--high);     border: 1px solid var(--high-bd); }
        .sev-medium   { background: var(--medium-bg);   color: var(--medium);   border: 1px solid var(--medium-bd); }
        .sev-info     { background: var(--info-bg);     color: var(--info);     border: 1px solid var(--info-bd); }
        .owasp-tag { font-size: 0.65rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--purple-mid); background: var(--purple-pale); border: 1px solid rgba(109,40,217,0.2); border-radius: 5px; padding: 2px 7px; white-space: nowrap; }
        .chevron { color: var(--gray-500); font-size: 0.8rem; transition: transform 0.2s; margin-left: 4px; flex-shrink: 0; }

        .vuln-card-body { padding: 0 20px 18px 42px; display: none; }
        .vuln-card-body.open { display: block; }
        .vuln-desc { font-size: 0.84rem; color: var(--gray-700); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 12px; }
        .vuln-meta { display: flex; gap: 20px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 10px; padding-top: 10px; border-top: 1px solid var(--gray-200); }
        .meta-item { font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--gray-500); display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 5px; }
        .meta-item strong { color: var(--black); }

        footer { background: var(--purple-deep); color: rgba(255,255,255,0.45); text-align: center; padding: 22px; font-size: 0.82rem; margin-top: 60px; }
        footer strong { color: var(--purple-light); }
    </style>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/mobile-responsive.css">
</head>
<body>

<!-- NAVBAR -->
<nav class="topbar">
    <div class="container">
        <a class="navbar-brand" href="/">Pwnshop<span class="dot"></span></a>
        <ul class="nav-right">
            <li><a class="nav-link-plain" href="/">Home</a></li>
            <% if (user) { %>
                <% if (user.role === 'admin') { %>
                    <li><a class="nav-link-plain" href="/admin/security">Audit Log</a></li>
                <% } %>
                <li><a href="/profile" class="user-chip"><%= user.username %></a></li>
                <li><a href="/logout" class="btn-logout">Logout</a></li>
            <% } else { %>
                <li><a class="nav-link-plain" href="/login">Login</a></li>
            <% } %>
        </ul>
    </div>
</nav>

<!-- HERO -->
<div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
        <div class="hero-eyebrow"><i class="bi bi-shield-exclamation"></i> Security Research</div>
        <h1 class="hero-title">Known Vulnerabilities</h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">
            Pwnshop is an intentionally vulnerable e-commerce application built for security training.
            The following vulnerabilities are present by design. Each one maps to a real-world weakness
            you will encounter in production systems.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-stats">
            <div class="hero-stat"><div class="num">41</div><div class="lbl">Total findings</div></div>
            <div class="hero-stat"><div class="num">35</div><div class="lbl">Web app vulns</div></div>
            <div class="hero-stat"><div class="num">6</div><div class="lbl">AI / LLM vulns</div></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="page-wrap">

    <!-- FILTER -->
    <div class="filter-bar">
        <button class="filter-btn active" onclick="filterAll(this)">All (41)</button>
        <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterType('web', this)">Web App (35)</button>
        <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterType('ai', this)">AI / LLM (6)</button>
        <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterSev('critical', this)">Critical</button>
        <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterSev('high', this)">High</button>
        <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterSev('medium', this)">Medium</button>
        <button class="filter-btn" onclick="filterSev('info', this)">Info</button>
    </div>

    <!-- ── A01: BROKEN ACCESS CONTROL ── -->
    <div class="cat-header" data-cat="access"><h2>A01:2025 · Broken Access Control</h2></div>

    <div class="vuln-card" data-type="web" data-sev="high">
        <div class="vuln-card-head" onclick="toggle(this)">
            <span class="vuln-id">PWN-001</span>
            <span class="vuln-title">IDOR — Order Details</span>
            <span class="owasp-tag">A01:2025</span>
            <span class="sev-badge sev-high">High</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="vuln-card-body">
            <p class="vuln-desc"><code>GET /order/:id</code> has no ownership check. Any authenticated user can view another user's order by incrementing the ID in the URL. Full order contents, shipping address, and payment amount are exposed.</p>
            <div class="vuln-meta">
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Endpoint:</strong> /order/:id</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Auth required:</strong> Yes</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Technique:</strong> IDOR / Parameter Tampering</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vuln-card" data-type="web" data-sev="high">
        <div class="vuln-card-head" onclick="toggle(this)">
            <span class="vuln-id">PWN-002</span>
            <span class="vuln-title">IDOR — Order Tracking (No Auth)</span>
            <span class="owasp-tag">A01:2025</span>
            <span class="sev-badge sev-high">High</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="vuln-card-body">
            <p class="vuln-desc"><code>POST /track</code> accepts an email address but never validates it against the order. Any order ID returns full results regardless of whose email is entered. <code>GET /track/:order_id</code> has no ownership check at all — no authentication required.</p>
            <div class="vuln-meta">
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Endpoint:</strong> /track, /track/:id</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Auth required:</strong> No</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Technique:</strong> IDOR</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vuln-card" data-type="web" data-sev="medium">
        <div class="vuln-card-head" onclick="toggle(this)">
            <span class="vuln-id">PWN-003</span>
            <span class="vuln-title">IDOR — Wishlist</span>
            <span class="owasp-tag">A01:2025</span>
            <span class="sev-badge sev-medium">Medium</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="vuln-card-body">
            <p class="vuln-desc"><code>GET /wishlist/:user_id</code> returns any user's wishlist with no auth or ownership check. Reveals product preferences and shopping behaviour of any user by changing the ID in the URL.</p>
            <div class="vuln-meta">
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Endpoint:</strong> /wishlist/:user_id</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Auth required:</strong> No</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Technique:</strong> IDOR</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vuln-card" data-type="web" data-sev="high">
        <div class="vuln-card-head" onclick="toggle(this)">
            <span class="vuln-id">PWN-004</span>
            <span class="vuln-title">IDOR — PwnMail Inbox</span>
            <span class="owasp-tag">A01:2025</span>
            <span class="sev-badge sev-high">High</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="vuln-card-body">
            <p class="vuln-desc"><code>GET /mail/:user_id</code> has no ownership check. Any authenticated user can read another user's inbox — including OTP codes and password reset tokens — by changing the user ID in the URL.</p>
            <div class="vuln-meta">
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Endpoint:</strong> /mail/:user_id</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Auth required:</strong> Partial</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Impact:</strong> Account takeover</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vuln-card" data-type="web" data-sev="info">
        <div class="vuln-card-head" onclick="toggle(this)">
            <span class="vuln-id">PWN-005</span>
            <span class="vuln-title">Public Audit Log — No Authentication</span>
            <span class="owasp-tag">A01:2025</span>
            <span class="sev-badge sev-info">Info</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="vuln-card-body">
            <p class="vuln-desc"><code>GET /logs</code> returns the full security audit log as JSON with no authentication required. Contains all login attempts, failed passwords, SSRF targets, XSS payloads, and admin actions.</p>
            <div class="vuln-meta">
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Endpoint:</strong> /logs</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Auth required:</strong> No</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Technique:</strong> IDOR / Unauthenticated Access</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── A05: SECURITY MISCONFIGURATION ── -->
    <div class="cat-header"><h2>A02:2025 · Security Misconfiguration</h2></div>

    <div class="vuln-card" data-type="web" data-sev="critical">
        <div class="vuln-card-head" onclick="toggle(this)">
            <span class="vuln-id">PWN-018</span>
            <span class="vuln-title">Debug Endpoint — Credentials Exposed Publicly</span>
            <span class="owasp-tag">A02:2025</span>
            <span class="sev-badge sev-critical">Critical</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="vuln-card-body">
            <p class="vuln-desc"><code>GET /debug/info</code> is publicly accessible with no authentication and returns the database hostname, username, database name, session secret, Node.js version, and platform. No credentials required.</p>
            <div class="vuln-meta">
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Endpoint:</strong> /debug/info</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Auth required:</strong> No</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Chains with:</strong> PWN-006 (session forgery)</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vuln-card" data-type="web" data-sev="medium">
        <div class="vuln-card-head" onclick="toggle(this)">
            <span class="vuln-id">PWN-019</span>
            <span class="vuln-title">Verbose Error Stack Traces in Responses</span>
            <span class="owasp-tag">A02:2025</span>
            <span class="sev-badge sev-medium">Medium</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="vuln-card-body">
            <p class="vuln-desc">The global error handler renders the full Node.js stack trace directly to the browser. Several routes also return raw <code>err.sqlMessage</code> output, revealing table names, column names, and query structure to attackers.</p>
            <div class="vuln-meta">
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Location:</strong> Global error handler + login/search routes</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Impact:</strong> Information disclosure</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vuln-card" data-type="web" data-sev="info">
        <div class="vuln-card-head" onclick="toggle(this)">
            <span class="vuln-id">PWN-020</span>
            <span class="vuln-title">No Security Headers</span>
            <span class="owasp-tag">A02:2025</span>
            <span class="sev-badge sev-info">Info</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="vuln-card-body">
            <p class="vuln-desc">The application sets no security-related HTTP headers. Missing: <code>Content-Security-Policy</code>, <code>X-Frame-Options</code>, <code>X-Content-Type-Options</code>, <code>Referrer-Policy</code>, and <code>Strict-Transport-Security</code>.</p>
            <div class="vuln-meta">
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Impact:</strong> Enables clickjacking, MIME sniffing, XSS amplification</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>


    <div class="vuln-card" data-type="web" data-sev="high">
        <div class="vuln-card-head" onclick="toggle(this)">
            <span class="vuln-id">PWN-038</span>
            <span class="vuln-title">Path Traversal — Invoice Download</span>
            <span class="owasp-tag">A02:2025</span>
            <span class="sev-badge sev-high">High</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="vuln-card-body">
            <p class="vuln-desc">The PDF invoice download endpoint at <code>GET /download?file=invoices/23.pdf</code> joins the <code>file</code> parameter directly onto a base directory using <code>path.join()</code> with no resolved-path validation. The <code>invoices/</code> prefix in the URL acts as a natural discovery hint — students who see the pattern can replace the filename with traversal sequences to escape the base directory entirely.</p>
            <div class="vuln-meta">
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Endpoint:</strong> GET /download?file=</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Auth required:</strong> Yes (any user)</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Payload:</strong> /download?file=invoices/../../../../../../../../etc/passwd</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Impact:</strong> Arbitrary file read — /etc/passwd, .env, app.js</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── A03:2025 · SOFTWARE SUPPLY CHAIN / OUTDATED COMPONENTS ── -->
    <div class="cat-header" data-type="web"><h2>A03:2025 · Software Supply Chain Failures</h2></div>

    <div class="vuln-card" data-type="web" data-sev="high">
        <div class="vuln-card-head" onclick="toggle(this)">
            <span class="vuln-id">PWN-041</span>
            <span class="vuln-title">Prototype Pollution — Vulnerable lodash Dependency</span>
            <span class="owasp-tag">A03:2025</span>
            <span class="sev-badge sev-high">High</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="vuln-card-body">
            <p class="vuln-desc">Pwnshop uses <code>lodash@4.17.4</code> which is vulnerable to prototype pollution (CVE-2019-10744). The search filter preferences endpoint passes user-supplied JSON directly to <code>_.merge()</code> with no sanitisation. Sending <code>__proto__</code> as a key poisons <code>Object.prototype</code> — every plain object created anywhere in the process inherits the injected property for the lifetime of the server.</p>
            <div class="vuln-meta">
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>CVE:</strong> CVE-2019-10744</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Endpoint:</strong> POST /search/filters</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Payload:</strong> {"__proto__": {"isAdmin": true}}</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Verify:</strong> GET /search/filters — injected property appears on the returned object</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── A02: CRYPTOGRAPHIC FAILURES ── -->
    <div class="cat-header"><h2>A04:2025 · Cryptographic Failures</h2></div>

    <div class="vuln-card" data-type="web" data-sev="critical">
        <div class="vuln-card-head" onclick="toggle(this)">
            <span class="vuln-id">PWN-006</span>
            <span class="vuln-title">Weak Session Secret — Hardcoded & Publicly Exposed</span>
            <span class="owasp-tag">A04:2025</span>
            <span class="sev-badge sev-critical">Critical</span>
            <i class="bi bi-chevron-down chevron"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="vuln-card-body">
            <p class="vuln-desc">The Express session is signed with <code>weak-secret-123</code>. This secret is also returned verbatim by <code>GET /debug/info</code>. Knowing the secret allows forging arbitrary session cookies to impersonate any user including admins.</p>
            <div class="vuln-meta">
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Location:</strong> app.js session config</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Chains with:</strong> PWN-018 (debug endpoint)</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Impact:</strong> Full account takeover</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vuln-card" data-type="web" data-sev="medium">
        <div class="vuln-card-head" onclick="toggle(this)">
            <span class="vuln-id">PWN-007</span>
