        <div class="vuln-card-body">
            <p class="vuln-desc">Coupons enforce per-user limits and category restrictions — but only at apply time, not at checkout. The bypass: apply a category-restricted coupon while the required item is in your cart, then remove that item before completing the order. The discount persists through to payment because the server never re-validates the category restriction at checkout.</p>
            <div class="vuln-meta">
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Endpoint:</strong> POST /apply-coupon → POST /checkout</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Technique:</strong> Business logic bypass — apply-time vs checkout-time validation gap</span>
                <span class="meta-item"><strong>Steps:</strong> Add phones item + other items → apply PHONES coupon → remove phones item → checkout at discounted price</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="vuln-card" data-type="web" data-sev="medium">
        <div class="vuln-card-head" onclick="toggle(this)">
